    "name": "app",
    "src": "package Main;\nimport Core.Output;\n\n// A self-contained program built into a standalone executable with `phg build`.\n// The produced binary embeds this source (in a CRC-guarded `.phorj` object-file\n// section) and runs it on the bytecode VM at startup — no Phorj install needed.\n\nfunction fib(int n): int {\n    if (n < 2) {\n        return n;\n    }\n    return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2);\n}\n\nfunction main(): void {\n    Output.printLine(\"phorj standalone build\");\n    for (int i in 0..10) {\n        Output.printLine(\"fib({i}) = {fib(i)}\");\n    }\n}"
